{"id": "819", "instruction": "Given $L$ as the part of the ellipse $frac{{{x}^{2}}}{{{a}^{2}}}+frac{{{y}^{2}}}{{{b}^{2}}}=1$ in the first quadrant, the value of the line integral $int_{L}{xydl}$ is ( ).\n\nOptions:\nA. $frac{a^2b^2({a^2}+ab+{b^2})}{3(a+b)}$\nB. $0$\nC. $frac{{{a}^{2}}+ab+{{b}^{2}}}{3(a+b)}$\nD. $frac{ab({{a}^{2}}+ab+{{b}^{2}})}{3(a+b)}$\nE. $frac{ab({a^2}+ab+{b^2})}{3(a+b)^2}$\nF. $frac{{{a}^{2}}{{b}^{2}}({{a}^{2}}+ab+{{b}^{2}})}{3(a+b)}$\nG. $frac{a^2b({a^2}+ab+{b^2})}{3(a+b)}$\nH. $frac{a{{b}^{2}}({{a}^{2}}+ab+{{b}^{2}})}{3(a+b)}$\nI. $frac{a^2b^2({a^2}+ab+{b^2})}{3(a+b)^2}$\nJ. $frac{a^2b({a^2}+ab+{b^2})}{3(a+b)^2}$", "output": "D"}
